




Here is my Multi-Branch Core Banking System with:

01. Modules (14)
02. Key Architectural Components(5) and 
03. Module Interdependencies(3)


---------------

## Total: 14 Core Modules

### 1. User Management Module
- User creation, editing, activation/deactivation
- Password reset functionality
- Failed login attempt management (3 wrong attempts → 5-minute lock)
- Branch-wise user assignment

### 2. Customer Management Module
- New customer registration (by Checker)
- Customer approval/rejection (by Maker)
- Customer activation/deactivation (by BrAdmin)
- KYC information management

### 3. Account Management Module
- Savings (111) and Current (222) account creation
- Automatic 5-digit account number generation
- Account activation/deactivation

### 4. Transaction Processing Module
- Deposit Transactions:
  - Account validation (active status)
  - Teller limit, branch limit, transaction limit checks
  - Positive amount validation
  
- Withdrawal Transactions:
  - Sufficient balance verification
  - Cash drawer availability check
  - Branch vault transfer (if needed)

### 5. Approval Workflow Module
- Checker → Maker workflow
- Batch number generation
- Transaction status management (Initiated/Approved/Rejected)
- Customer registration approval

### 6. Cash Management Module
- Cash drawer balance tracking
- Teller-specific cash limits
- Branch vault balance management
- End-of-day cash proof

### 7. Sub-Ledger Module
- Customer Ledger management
- Cash/Teller Ledger management
- Running balance calculation
- Statement generation

### 8. General Ledger Module
- GL Head management (by HoSuperAdmin)
- Double-entry accounting posting
- GL journal entries
- Atomicity assurance (COMMIT/ROLLBACK)

### 9. Reconciliation Module
- Sub-Ledger vs GL reconciliation
- Control account verification:
  - GL-1001 (Cash) vs Σ(Cash Drawers)
  - GL-2001 (Customer Deposits) vs Σ(Customer Accounts)
- Trial Balance preparation

### 10. Audit & Monitoring Module
- Audit log maintenance
- User activity tracking
- Exception reporting
- Pending postings monitoring

### 11. Reporting Module
- Customer statements (with double-entry view)
- Financial statements (Assets & Liabilities)
- Trial Balance reports
- Reconciliation reports
- Daily transaction reports

### 12. System Control Module
- GL posting process lock/unlock
- End-of-Day (EOD) processing
- Branch-wise system configuration

### 13. Role-Based Access Control Module
- Checker: Customer creation, transaction initiation
- Maker: Approval/rejection, edit/delete before approval
- Branch Admin: GL posting, branch management
- Head Office Super Admin: System-wide control
- Auditor: Monitoring and reporting

### 14. Validation & Integrity Module
- Pre-transaction condition validation
- Concurrency/race condition prevention
- Data integrity assurance
- Transaction boundary management




######################################################################################################
                    Key Architectural Components (Implied from Requirements):
######################################################################################################

### 1. Authentication & Authorization Module
- Cookie-based authentication with Claims
- Role-based permission system
- Session management

### 2. Database Transaction Module
- MySQL transaction management
- Deadlock prevention
- ACID compliance implementation

### 3. PDF Generation Module
- Customer statement PDF generation
- Financial report PDF export
- Reconciliation report PDF creation

### 4. Batch Processing Module
- Batch number generation system
- Bulk transaction handling
- Scheduled posting processes

### 5. Exception Handling Module
- Mismatch detection and correction workflow
- Suspense account management
- Error logging and notification

---

########################################################################
                    Module Interdependencies:
########################################################################

1. Transaction Flow: Checker → Maker → Sub-Ledger → General Ledger → Reconciliation
2. User Hierarchy: HoSuperAdmin → BrAdmin → Maker → Checker → Customer
3. Data Flow: Frontend → Business Logic → Database → Reporting → Audit






.
